headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony hits winning layup with 1.3 seconds left, Magic complete 21-point rally to beat Nets 102-101

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton scored 31 points and the Indiana Pacers rebounded from a 37-point loss to Boston two nights earlier by beating the Celtics 123-114 on Sunday night in the rematch.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haliburton scores 31 points as Pacers rebound from 37-point loss to Celtics by winning rematch

headlines.description: — Trae Young had 34 points and 10 assists, De’Andre Hunter scored 22 points and the Atlanta Hawks routed the Toronto Raptors 136-107 on Sunday night for their fourth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young scores 34 as Hawks beat Raptors 136-107, hand Raptors 10th consecutive loss

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored 27 points before being one of seven people ejected, six for their roles in a fight in the final minute of the Miami Heat's 104-100 victory over the Houston Rockets on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro leads Heat over Rockets in game marred by fight and ejections in final minute

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 35 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder won their 11th straight game, beating the short-handed Memphis Grizzlies 130-106 on Sunday night in a matchup of Western Conference leaders that turned lopsided before halftime.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder rout short-handed Grizzlies 130-106 for their 11th straight victory

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Donte DiVincenzo scored 26 points as the Minnesota Timberwolves defeated the San Antonio Spurs 112-110 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DiVincenzo scores 26 to lead Timberwolves past Spurs 112-110 despite 34 points from Wembanyama
